programme.title: Sleuths, Spies & Sorcerers: Andrew Marr's Paperback Heroes: Detectives
programme.desc: The broadcaster explores the genres of fiction that are the most popular with the general public, unpicking their conventions to show why they are such page-turners. He begins by looking at detective novels, profiling pioneers Agatha Christie, Dashiell Hammett and Ruth Rendell, and decoding set-pieces such as Hercule Poirot's drawing room denouements and the locked room mysteries of John Dickson Carr. With contributions by Ian Rankin, Sophie Hannah, Anthony Horowitz and Val McDermid

programme.title: Great British Railway Journeys: Urmston to New Islington
programme.sub-title: Urmston to New Islington Season 14, Episode 2
programme.desc: Michael Portillo's railway journey reaches Greater Manchester, where he celebrates new beginnings for the nation in the years after the Second World War. At Trafford General Hospital, he investigates the birth of the National Health Service. A retired physiotherapist recalls her part in the historic event of July 5, 1948. Coronation Star tells Michael about the first episode of the soap, broadcast live in 1960. And at the city's Science and Industry Museum, the presenter encounters a replica of the Baby, which was created in 1948 - the first machine in the world to run a stored program and the forerunner of all modern computers

programme.title: Wainwright Walks: Catbells
programme.desc: Julia Bradbury travels by boat and foot as she explores Catbells fell, situated on the shore of Derwentwater near the Lakeland town of Keswick. The presenter discovers the secrets of the classic climb, learning miners once trod the paths in search of minerals more valuable than gold

programme.title: Wainwright: The Man Who Loved the Lakes
programme.desc: Part-dramatised profile of writer and artist Alfred Wainwright, the enthusiastic fell-walker from Blackburn who became renowned for his pictorial guides to the English Lake District. More than two million copies have been sold since he began writing them in 1955, and they have become the standard reference work for the area

programme.title: The Bermuda Triangle: Beneath the Waves
programme.desc: Bruce Denardo explores the legend of the region where many planes and ships have disappeared in mysterious circumstances. Using a state-of-the-art submarine, Graham Hawkes reveals how five wrecks ended up 730ft down in the heart of the deadly expanse of water

programme.title: Great British Railway Journeys: Oldham to Wakefield
programme.desc: Michael Portillo travels by tram to the former cotton town of Oldham on the edge of the Peak District. Here he visits Oldham Coliseum, the town's Victorian repertory theatre, and hears about the lifting of censorship by the Lord Chamberlain's Office in the late 1960s. He then goes hiking before a visit to Sheffield, where he attends a knife-making workshop. He ends this part of his journey admiring the striking post-war sculptures of Barbara Hepworth at the Yorkshire Sculpture Park near Wakefield

programme.title: Wainwright Walks: Crinkle Crags and Bow Fell
programme.sub-title: Crinkle Crags and Bow Fell Season 2, Episode 3
programme.desc: Julia Bradbury attempts to make her way along a scenic ridge-mile in Lakeland as she retraces the walks and climbs of Alfred Wainwright. She reaches the summits of Crinkle Crags and Bow Fell, two of the highest peaks in the region

programme.title: The Stuarts in Exile: A New Hope
programme.desc: Part two of two. Dr Clare Jackson reveals how the Jacobite campaign took place on a European-wide stage, rather than purely Scottish, and inspired a nexus of international intrigue and covert plots. Jackson explores why so many law-abiding Scots and English were prepared to support the Catholic Stuarts and how the new Protestant Hanoverian regime hung by a thread, as George I and II struggled to impose their authority on frequently hostile and anti-European subjects

programme.title: Wogan: 06/11/1987
programme.desc: Terry Wogan is joined by dancer and actress Moira Shearer, choreographer Gillian Lynne, film director James Ivory, actress Hayley Mills and singer Kit Harvey, who also sings Trashy Novels with his group Kit & the Widow. First broadcast November 1987

programme.title: Artworks Scotland: Moira Shearer: The Reluctant Star
programme.sub-title: Moira Shearer: The Reluctant Star Season 1, Episode 1
programme.desc: A tribute to Moira Shearer, arguably Scotland's greatest ballerina, who died earlier this year. The programme charts her reluctance to accept the fame her celluloid role in The Red Shoes brought her. Featuring contributions by family and friends, including her husband of 55 years Ludovic Kennedy

programme.title: The Red Shoes
programme.desc: A budding prima ballerina is set to achieve her dream of stardom when she decides to leave her prestigious company to marry a composer - a decision that enrages her possessive mentor, who vows revenge. Powell and Pressburger's drama, based on the story by Hans Christian Andersen, starring Anton Walbrook, Moira Shearer, Marius Goring, Robert Helpmann and Albert Basserman

programme.title: Things You Should Have Done: Do Something Entrepreneurial
programme.desc: Dave cannot keep up with the mortgage on his single wage, and faces the very real threat of having to move in with Chi. Unable to cope with their debts, the family seek help from Ruth, who advises them to be entrepreneurial. Dave reveals he has a very rich estranged sister whom he hasn't spoken to since Brexit, but who may well be the solution to their crisis

Meanwhile, James May spends time at Camp Bastion in Afghanistan to learn about the army's vehicle redeployment efforts, and actor Tom Hiddleston tries to coax the best time he can muster from the Reasonably Priced Car

programme.title: Miami Vice
programme.desc: Narcotics detectives Crockett and Tubbs go undercover and pose as smugglers to infiltrate a powerful drug cartel. However, the operation is threatened when Crockett becomes dangerously involved with the wife of the organisation's ringleader. Michael Mann's crime thriller based on the 1980s TV series, starring Colin Farrell, Jamie Foxx, Gong Li, Naomie Harris and Luis Tosar

programme.title: Things You Should Have Done: Get Therapy
programme.desc: Sitcom, starring Lucia Keskin as a dependent young woman learning to fend for herself after her parents' deaths. When the family faces another unexpected bereavement, Chi returns to her list of things you should have done, and opts to get therapy. Bridget Christie joins the cast as a tough-love grief counsellor, who adopts questionable methods in helping Chi move on

programme.title: Things You Should Have Done: Do Something Entrepreneurial
programme.desc: Dave cannot keep up with the mortgage on his single wage, and faces the very real threat of having to move in with Chi. Unable to cope with their debts, the family seek help from Ruth, who advises them to be entrepreneurial. Dave reveals he has a very rich estranged sister whom he hasn't spoken to since Brexit, but who may well be the solution to their crisis

programme.title: Things You Should Have Done: Give Back to Others
programme.sub-title: Give Back to Others Season 2, Episode 3
programme.desc: Ruth tells Chi that multiple bereavements in rapid succession is no excuse for feeling sorry for yourself. She sets her the task of comparing herself to those less fortunate by helping out at a food bank. Dave and Lucas have only 10 to their name, and settle for a dinner of bread and cress. Comedian Sarah Kendall reprises her role from series one, in an episode she co-wrote

programme.title: The Beauty Queen and the Catfish: Turning Detective
programme.desc: Abbie Draper takes her findings to the police, but they are unable to do anything about it and the Catfish of Kilmarnock remains free to target more and more victims. However, Abbie cannot walk away and steps up her investigation over months that turn into years, with victims spread across the country and dating back over a decade

programme.title: Top Gear
programme.desc: Jeremy Clarkson, Richard Hammond and James May immerse themselves in nostalgia and try to prove that hot hatches from their younger days are better than their modern equivalents. Jeremy grabs the keys to a Volkswagen Golf GTI, Richard takes the wheel of a Vauxhall Nova SRi and James May opts for the Ford Fiesta XR2i, and the trio set off on a road trip that includes a hill climb and a visit to a supermarket. However, their adventure concludes at an army training ground in Wales, where they and their steeds must face the heavily armed Top Gear Police Department. Downton Abbey star Hugh Bonneville blasts the Reasonably Priced Car around the test track

programme.title: SpongeBob SquarePants: Bottle Burglars
programme.desc: Plankton steals the secret formula with some unwitting help from SpongeBob and Squidward, who plan to break in to the Chum Bucket and steal it back

programme.title: Sort Your Life Out with Stacey Solomon: Is It a Bedroom, Or Is It a Garage?
programme.sub-title: Is It a Bedroom, Or Is It a Garage?
programme.desc: The team help the Jamiesons from East Sussex transform the home that's been in their family for 40 years. They strip every item from the converted bungalow and display them all in a warehouse where they discover 106 animal ornaments, 87 board games and over 1,000 pieces of china. As they sort through the decades of keepsakes, mum Nadine reflects on her childhood and the challenges of raising her daughters

programme.title: Stacey Dooley: Costa del Narcos
programme.desc: The presenter reports on how southern Spain has become the main gateway for drugs into Europe, leading to violent turf wars between gangs and a government crackdown as the police struggle to regain control of their streets. Stacey goes on aerial patrol with police officers guarding the strip of water between Morocco and Spain, and discovers the extraordinary lengths smugglers will take to evade them, including travelling at 100mph in speedboats during extreme weather conditions

programme.title: Our Girl: Nepal Tour
programme.desc: Georgie and 2 Section are sent to Nepal following a devastating earthquake, where she quickly discovers that disaster brings out the worst as well as the best in people. In addition to her duties as a medic, Georgie is tasked with mentoring Maisie, a reckless young recruit, and also meets Milan, an attractive Nepalese engineer, with whom she forms a bond while working together to rebuild the area

programme.title: Our Girl: Nepal Tour
programme.desc: A frantic search ensues in the wake of the aftershock when 2-section realise Georgie is missing, while a young local girl previously befriended by Georgie, and a small group of children, are abducted by Da Chand, a fake NGO worker. Military intelligence discovers that he's part of a terrorist network and there's a chance he will lead them to the more important target of Aatan Omar, leaving 2-section to track him and to assist a Special Forces Unit led by a familiar and unwelcome face - Elvis

programme.title: Kindling
programme.desc: Upon learning their friend has a terminal illness, a group of mates return home to fulfil his final wishes. Coming-of-age drama inspired by true events, starring George Somner, Conrad Khan, Wilson Mbomio and Mia McKenna-Bruce

programme.title: The Piano
programme.desc: A mute Scottish widow travels to New Zealand with her daughter, and enters into a loveless arranged marriage. Her one means of self-expression is her piano, which her husband sells to a gruff settler who has adopted Maori culture. He allows her to play the instrument, and through their shared love of music, a passionate affair develops. Period drama, starring Oscar-winners Holly Hunter and Anna Paquin. With Harvey Keitel and Sam Neill

programme.title: What We Do in the Shadows: Headhunting
programme.desc: Guillermo gets a new job, and Colin helps Laszlo make a new friend. Comedy, starring Matt Berry, Mark Proksch and Harvey Guilln

programme.title: The Traitors
programme.desc: The traitors' latest gameplay makes the faithful more determined than ever to uncover their identity and the mission puts the traitors under intense pressure, which continues to build at the round table as everyone attempts to deflect scrutiny

programme.title: Can You Keep a Secret?
programme.desc: Debbie bans William from chocolate and Harry from sharing their secret with Neha. But someone else now knows about William - and wants a cut of the cash

programme.title: Amanda & Alan's Greek Job
programme.desc: Inspired by Gerald Durrell's love of wildlife, Amanda and Alan design their first ever children's bedroom and visit Gerald's widow Lee for inspiration. Amanda calls in help to build a bespoke L-shaped bunk bed while Alan pulls a shift at the donkey sanctuary before the pair swap out their boiler suits for swim suits and head to Corfu's famous water park Aqualand

Izzie Balmer and JJ Chalmers uncover treasures to raise the money required, from a neglected trike motorcycle to vintage watches

Michael finds an impressive scent bottle, and Caroline gets a glimpse into the past by looking through a stereoscopic viewer. Paul also looks around the property, and meets the current owner, Lord Edward Manners

programme.desc: Nadia Jae, Tamzin Outhwaite, Nigel Planer and Steen Raskopoulos test their general knowledge skills in a variety of trivia-based games

A session making and painting Roman-style pots ends their weekend escape

programme.title: Winterwatch

programme.title: A House Through Time
programme.desc: It's 1940, and in London, the threat of invasion by Germany has become very real. Montagu Mansions resident Timothy Corsellis begins training as an RAF pilot, but begins to regret his decision when facing the prospect of bombing innocent civilians. His older sister, Mary, gets involved in supporting victims of the bombing in Stepney

programme.title: Digging for Britain: A Mysterious Bone Box and Admiral Nelson's Favourite Ship
programme.sub-title: A Mysterious Bone Box and Admiral Nelson's Favourite Ship
programme.desc: Featuring an ft slipway in the New Forest where Admiral Nelson's favourite ship was built, an Anglo-Saxon cemetery where a host of well-preserved and rare objects have been found, and finds from Trinity College, Oxford. Plus, a late Roman cemetery that features an intricate bone box and part of a Roman bone flute, and a tangle of delicate Iron Age objects that have to be carefully micro-excavated in Kent

programme.title: One Foot in the Grave: The Valley of Fear
programme.sub-title: The Valley of Fear Season 1, Episode 3
programme.desc: The Meldrew household is disrupted by a pesky plumber whose penchant for morbid practical jokes would try the patience of a saint. Victor decides it's time to call a neighbourhood watch system after he's mugged and graffiti is spray painted on the side of the Meldrews' house. David Renwick's award-winning comedy, starring Richard Wilson and Annette Crosbie

programme.desc: The BBC's world affairs editor reflects on the week's major global news stories, talking to local experts from around the world to go behind the headlines

programme.title: The Road Dance
programme.desc: Kirsty Macleod dreams of a better life away from the isolation that suffocates her in a small village on an island in the Outer Hebrides. Suppressing these aspirations, she sees her lover Murdo conscripted for service in the First World War, soon to set off and fight alongside the other young men from the village. A dance is held in their honour the evening before they depart, and it's on this fateful night that Kirsty's life takes a dramatic and tragic turn. Period drama, starring Hermione Corfield

programme.title: Mystery Road: Origin
programme.desc: Jay refuses to write off a suspicious death, while Mary does some sleuthing of her own. Drama, starring Mark Coles Smith, Tuuli Narkle and Robyn Malcolm

programme.title: Inside the Factory: Oven Chips
programme.desc: Paddy McGuinness and Cherry Healey visit the McCain factory near Scarborough that cuts, fries and freezes 80 million chips every single day. Paddy follows one delivery of potatoes through the factory and out the other side to a truck waiting to take chips to customers, a process which takes just two hours and creates 1.7million chips. Cherry learns about the science behind malt vinegar production and Ruth Goodman explores the origins of fish and chips

programme.title: NASA's Unexplained Files

programme.desc: After witnessing agricultural practices in far-flung places like Bhutan and Okinawa, host Mike dives into the world of sustainable gardening right in his own backyard. With the guidance of a local soil scientist, we follow Mike's hands-on journey into the art and science of farming sustainably. From planting the first seeds to navigating unexpected challenges, this episode offers a candid look at the highs and lows of gardening for sustainability. Beyond the physical labor and the harvest, we also explore the emotional and mental rewards of this earthy endeavor. Mike learns that the act of growing your own food is not just a means to an endit's a therapeutic practice that nurtures the mind as well as the body. Tune in to see how the simple act of cultivating a garden can yield abundant lessons in sustainability, health, and well-being.

programme.title: Health Explored
programme.desc: We embark on a unique journey around the world to film our series but behind the scenes explore the effects of stress on the human body. Equipped with cutting-edge Hexo Skin sensors and other wearable tech, we subject ourselves to adrenaline-pumping activities like skydiving and roller coaster rides, as well as draining experiences like red-eye flights. By monitoring real-time data, we gain fascinating insights into how various stressors impact our physiological responses. From heart rate fluctuations to sleep monitoring this episode reveals how stress can be both an exhilarating and exhausting experience. As we push the limits of adventureand our own comfort zoneswe discover that creating a health series can be a surprisingly stressful endeavor in itself. Tune in to uncover the multifaceted impact of stress on our well-being and learn what we can do to manage it effectively.

programme.desc: Kellie Pickler comes to a rehearsal to share her experience and motivate the girls as Training Camp is coming to an end. Melissa Rycroft makes Kelsey aware of a big mistake. Candace Romo helps with a big night of cuts.

programme.title: Dallas Cowboys Cheerleaders: Making the Team
programme.desc: Squad announcement is bittersweet as some favorites go home. The team has their first appearance at the Star Ribbon cutting. Game Day is when dreams come true!

programme.title: Dallas Cowboys Cheerleaders: Making the Team
programme.desc: Hundreds of beautiful and talented women converge on AT&T Stadium to start the hardest audition process in professional sports, trying out for a coveted spot on the most famous NFL cheerleading squad in the world, the Dallas Cowboys Cheerleaders.

programme.title: Dallas Cowboys Cheerleaders: Making the Team
programme.desc: With the field narrowed down to 119 women, the pressure is on. They must quickly learn a power pom routine and the famous kickline in order to perform it an hour later before the judges.

programme.title: Dallas Cowboys Cheerleaders: Making the Team
programme.desc: The veterans finally enter the audition process. Now all 83 women are judged head to head during a panel interview, a solo dance performance and on their appearance on the football field as seen and the big screen.

programme.title: Dallas Cowboys Cheerleaders: Making the Team
programme.desc: 44 women begin the very first training camp at the new 1 billion dollar Cowboys' facility, The Star. At the First Meeting, Kelli lays down the law and makes it clear that eight women will be sent home this summer.

programme.title: Dallas Cowboys Cheerleaders: Making the Team
programme.desc: First, the ladies need to have the "classic look" of a Dallas Cowboys Cheerleader. Kelli's hair and make-up transformations are legendary. The ladies are also assessed through a new state of the art fitness test, "Styku".

programme.title: Dallas Cowboys Cheerleaders: Making the Team
programme.desc: Kelli media trains the rookie candidates to determine who best represents the DCC at press events. NBC news anchor, Meredith Land tests their on-camera interview skills.

programme.title: Dallas Cowboys Cheerleaders: Making the Team

programme.title: Dallas Cowboys Cheerleaders: Making the Team

programme.title: Dallas Cowboys Cheerleaders: Making the Team
programme.desc: The squad goes on an appearance to support pop music star, Demi Lovato. The ladies learn the entrance to the famed pre-game dance. It's a make or break moment. If a woman can't learn it quickly it might be her last night.

programme.title: Dallas Cowboys Cheerleaders: Making the Team

programme.title: Dallas Cowboys Cheerleaders: Making the Team

programme.title: Dallas Cowboys Cheerleaders: Making the Team

Western, directed by and starring Clint Eastwood, alongside Verna Bloom and Marianna Hill

programme.title: Sky Cinema Preview-Jan 2026
programme.desc: A look at some of the films on Sky in January

programme.title: Long Gone Heroes
programme.desc: A battle-hardened special forces operative attempts to rescue his kidnapped niece when a mercenary mission spirals into chaos. Action thriller, starring Eden Brolin, Andy Garcia and Melissa Leo

programme.title: Shenandoah
programme.desc: A Virginian farmer is left to raise seven children after his wife dies. He tries to keep his family out of the American Civil War, but when Union troops abduct his son, and his son-in-law enlists with the Confederates, he is unable to maintain his neutral stance and is dragged into the conflict. Western, starring James Stewart, Doug McClure, Rosemary Forsyth, Katharine Ross and Patrick Wayne

programme.title: Cleaner

programme.title: Batman
programme.desc: The masked avenger stalks the streets of Gotham City, waging a nightly war against the criminal element. However, he may have met his match when the city's crime syndicate is taken over by the crazed Joker, who plans to poison the populace with toxic chemicals. Tim Burton's comic-book adventure, starring Michael Keaton, Jack Nicholson and Kim Basinger

programme.title: Batman Returns
programme.desc: The masked hero returns to face the Penguin, a grotesque crime boss dwelling in the sewers who conspires with a corrupt businessman to make himself mayor. When the tycoon tries to kill his secretary, she returns as vengeful vigilante Catwoman, who soon forms an intense relationship with the dark knight in both their costumed and real identities. Tim Burton's comic-book adventure sequel, starring Michael Keaton, Danny DeVito and Michelle Pfeiffer

programme.title: Batman & Robin
programme.desc: The caped crusader and his sidekick take on the villainous Mr Freeze, who plans to destroy Gotham City with an icy doomsday weapon unless his demands are met. The dynamic duo also have to contend with femme fatale Poison Ivy, who is determined to drive a wedge between them. Comic-book adventure, starring George Clooney, Arnold Schwarzenegger, Uma Thurman and Chris O'Donnell

programme.title: Batman Forever
programme.desc: The masked crimefighter takes on the twin threats of disfigured maniac Two-Face and insane genius the Riddler, who are plotting to control the brains of the entire world. Meanwhile, an acrobat whose family has been murdered by Two-Face steps up to join Batman in his fight against evil. Superhero adventure sequel, starring Val Kilmer, Tommy Lee Jones, Nicole Kidman, Jim Carrey and Chris O'Donnell

programme.title: Kong: Skull Island
programme.desc: Years after two enemy pilots land on a mysterious unchartered island in the Pacific, a team of scientists embark on a top-secret mission to the same region. Things soon descend into chaos when the local wildlife proves far from welcoming, and they must battle to escape from the domain of the mighty Kong. Action adventure, starring Tom Hiddleston, Samuel L Jackson and Brie Larson

programme.title: Rumble in the Bronx
programme.desc: A Hong Kong cop visits New York to attend the wedding of his uncle, who has just sold his market store to an entrepreneur. The policeman volunteers to stick around to help get the business running, but they soon fall foul of a local biker gang. Martial arts adventure, starring Jackie Chan, Anita Mui, Francoise Yip and Bill Tung. In Cantonese and English

programme.title: Terminator Salvation
programme.desc: In a world dominated by deadly robots, resistance leader John Connor fights to stop the creation of an advanced new terminator, and searches for the teenager destined to go back in time and become his father. Elsewhere, a mysterious stranger with no memory is about to learn the shocking truth about his origins. Sci-fi thriller sequel, starring Christian Bale, Sam Worthington and Anton Yelchin

programme.title: I, Tonya
programme.desc: Ice skater Tonya Harding rises through the ranks at the US figure skating championships, but her future in the sport is thrown into question by a shocking incident after her ex-husband steps in. Director Craig Gillespie's comedy biopic, starring Margot Robbie, Sebastian Stan, and Allison Janney, who won a Bafta and an Oscar for her performance

programme.title: Do the Right Thing
programme.desc: Racial tensions erupt in a Brooklyn neighbourhood on the hottest day of the summer. The simmering conflicts centre on the Italian-owned local pizza parlour, as a minor dispute gradually escalates into full-blown violence. Drama, directed by and starring Spike Lee, with Danny Aiello, John Turturro, Ossie Davis, Rosie Perez and Samuel L Jackson

programme.title: Chuck Chuck Baby
programme.desc: Helen lives with her ex-husband, his 20-year-old girlfriend, their new baby, and his dying mother Gwen. Helen's life is a grind, but she has a chance at romance when a secret love returns. Writer/director Janis Pugh's drama, starring Louise Brealey and Annabel Scholey

programme.title: Dear John
programme.desc: A soldier falls in love with a student he meets while on two weeks' leave, and he promises to seek her out after completing his tour of duty. However, in the aftermath of the September 11 attacks, he decides to re-enlist in the army, putting their relationship to the test. Romantic drama, with Channing Tatum and Amanda Seyfried

programme.title: Pawn Sacrifice
programme.desc: American chess prodigy Bobby Fischer challenges the best player in the Soviet Union in a top championship, causing the two nations to use the event to fuel their respective agendas. Fischer soon finds himself caught between the two superpowers as well as having to deal with his own struggles. Tobey Maguire and Liev Schreiber star in this fact-based sporting drama set in 1972 during the Cold War

programme.title: I Used to Be Funny
programme.desc: A stand-up comedian struggling with PTSD agonises over whether or not to join the search for a missing teenage girl she used to look after. Writer-director Ally Pankiw's comedy drama, starring Rachel Sennott and Olga Petsa

programme.title: Darkest Hour
programme.desc: May 1940. As the Nazis advance against Britain's European allies, newly elected prime minister Winston Churchill must decide whether to leave neighbouring countries to their fate, by striking a peace deal with Hitler, or fight on against terrifying odds for the greater good. Double Oscar and Bafta-winning period drama, starring Gary Oldman, Lily James and Kristin Scott Thomas

programme.title: The Boy in the Striped Pyjamas
programme.desc: Bruno, a boy in Nazi Germany, moves to the country when his father is placed in charge of a concentration camp. While exploring the woods close to the facility's boundary, he spots a Jewish youngster being held there, and the two become friends - but Bruno remains innocently oblivious to the camp's true purpose. Drama, starring David Thewlis, Asa Butterfield and Jack Scanlon

programme.title: Quartet
programme.desc: Three former opera singers prepare for their annual concert to mark Verdi's birthday and raise funds for their retirement home. However, this year, a famous diva has joined the group, and her history with the others threatens the performance. Comedy drama, directed by Dustin Hoffman and starring Maggie Smith, Billy Connolly, Tom Courtenay, Pauline Collins and Michael Gambon

Oscar-winning drama, starring Lady Gaga, Bradley Cooper, who also directed, and Sam Elliott

Erotic drama based on EL James' bestseller, starring Jamie Dornan and Dakota Johnson
